The government was Monday lauding its efforts to restore the credibility of exams with  education Cabinet  Secretary Amina Mohamed and KNEC chairman Prof. George Magoha saying the multi-agency approach had managed to curb cases on cheating. Speaking during the release of this year’s KCPE examination results, the two officials however faulted parents for  abdicating their duties leading to an upsurge in cases of teenage pregnancies.  